I just posted about my 2 grandaughters of whom I am desperately <br>
searching for but for My son Steve he was only 17 when he enlisted <br>
and was in Viet Nam on his 18th birthdaySepember 20/1968.I cannot imagine the horror that he went through.His nerve are shot but is able to work but has had a hard time coping with this terrible thing that happened to him.The Ohio Viet Nam Wall will be in Findlay, Ohio on May 9&amp;10 1997 and I have ordered a wreath to be placed there for our 17 Hardin County boys who was less fortunate than our son .Such a small gesture for me to do but I will never forget what you guys did for us in the name of USA.I am a devoted Christian and they talk about Hell well our family has been there with this loss of our loved Granddaughters.Thanks Guy &amp; Ladies who served<br>

